cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically on developing a framework for unsupervised learning of object prototypes. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic constructs such as Markov random fields, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The scalability and efficiency of the proposed framework suggest a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The use of unsupervised learning algorithms and the focus on discovering and modeling objects suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also discusses efficient algorithms for detection and localization, which suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL).
